# Metadata Dictionary

| Attribute        | Definition |
|------------------|-----------|
| Age | Patient’s age in years (numeric). |
| Sex | Biological sex of the patient (Male or Female). |
| ChestPainType | Type of chest pain: TA (Typical Angina – classic heart-related pain), ATA (Atypical Angina – non-classic pain), NAP (Non-Anginal Pain – not heart-related), ASY (Asymptomatic – no chest pain). |
| RestingBP | Resting blood pressure (mmHg): <120 normal, 120–129 elevated, 130–139 hypertension stage 1, ≥140 hypertension stage 2, ≥180 crisis. |
| Cholesterol | Serum cholesterol (mg/dL): <200 desirable, 200–239 borderline high, ≥240 high. |
| FastingBS | Fasting blood sugar: 0 = normal, 1 = prediabetes/diabetes. |
| RestingECG | Resting electrocardiogram results: Normal (no issues), ST (ST segment abnormality), LVH (left ventricular hypertrophy). |
| MaxHR | Maximum heart rate achieved (range: 60–202). |
| ExerciseAngina | Indicates if exercise induces angina (Yes or No). |
| Oldpeak | ST depression induced by exercise relative to rest (continuous values from -2.6 to 6.2). |
| ST_Slope | Slope of peak exercise ST segment: Up (normal), Flat (reduced blood flow), Down (abnormal, indicates heart disease). |
| HeartDisease | Target variable: 0 = No heart disease, 1 = Heart disease present. |
